# Token Beats backend base URL.
#
# Production (default if unset):
#   https://token-beats-api.jacky-1a4.workers.dev/v1/summary
#
# Staging (use for dev / preview deploys):
#   https://token-beats-api-staging.jacky-1a4.workers.dev/v1/summary
#
# Local dev (when you have `pnpm --filter @tokenbeats/api dev` running):
#   http://localhost:8787/v1/summary
VITE_TB_API_BASE=https://token-beats-api.jacky-1a4.workers.dev/v1/summary

# OPTIONAL — build-time credentials.
#
# When BOTH VITE_TB_USER and VITE_TB_TOKEN are set at build time,
# every fetch uses them and the sign-in modal is bypassed entirely.
# Convenient for a single-user personal deploy (e.g. tokens.jacky.jp
# pointing at your own account).
#
# SECURITY: anything in `VITE_*` is bundled into the public JS the
# browser downloads. Anyone visiting the site can read your token by
# opening devtools. ONLY use this on:
#   - a single-user deploy you fully control, AND
#   - a token whose only privilege is reading YOUR own usage data
#
# For shared / multi-user deployments, leave both unset and the
# localStorage + sign-in modal flow runs instead.
#
# Rotate by redeploying with a new VITE_TB_TOKEN.
# VITE_TB_USER=jacky@gcu.co.jp
# VITE_TB_TOKEN=
